# Docker build context exclusions for `fly deploy --config apps/realtime/fly.toml`.
# Without this, the entire repo (including every node_modules tree and .git)
# gets shipped to Fly's builder — slow + wasteful.
#
# Kept narrow on purpose: only obvious junk is excluded. The Dockerfile itself
# picks the subset of the repo it needs via explicit COPY directives.

# Dependency trees — re-installed inside the container
**/node_modules

# Build artifacts
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/dist
**/.tsbuildinfo
**/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
**/*.log

# Local env (NEVER ship secrets into the image — use fly secrets set instead)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Editor / VCS metadata
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store

# Repo-internal scratch
.claude
apps/workers/tmp
